[1] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Thu, 3 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency (Luanda) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200608030937.html>

In the past 24 hours, 7 cholera cases, without claiming any lives, have
been detected by health authorities of Luanda, in 3 of the 9 districts that
make up the Angolan capital. According to health authorities, 5 cases were
registered in Viana district, 1 in Sambizanga and the other in Rangel.
Since the outbreak in Feb 2006, 23 418 people were infected and 302 died.
Meanwhile, cholera cases in Luanda as in the remaining provinces of the
country might increase with the nearing rainy season.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola showing the location of the northern coastal location of
Luanda can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. The only 3
provinces yet to be reported involved are Cunene, Moxico, and Lunda Sul.
They also can be found on the map. - Mod.LL]
