[2] Cholera - Congo DR (North Kivu)
Date: Wed 3 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press Agency [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=460971>

Three people have died from a cholera epidemic in DR Congo's Mutwanga
health district of North-Kivu, health authorities said here on Wed 3 Aug
2006. The worst affected areas include Lubirihya on DR Congo's border with
Uganda, Kasindi-Port, a small coastal town on Edward Lake, and Mutwanga,
where 24 cases have been reported
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Congo DR showing the location of North Kivu on the border with
Uganda can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/drcongo.pdf> - Mod.LL]
