[3] Cholera - Uganda (Gulu)
Date: Sat, 29 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200607280877.html>

At least 10 cases of cholera have been reported in Gulu Municipality. The
secretary for health, Ms Santa Oketta, on 15 Jul 2006 identified the areas
affected by the disease as Kirombe, Kanyagoga, and Pece Pawel. She said
other 6 cases had been reported in Unyama IDP camp.
Mayor Christopher Acire urged health workers to sensitize residents on how
to contain the disease. Meanwhile, authorities in Adjumani town council
have closed over 20 eating places for lack of toilet facilities.
The town clerk, Mr Samuel Lagu, said the move was aimed at controlling the
spread of waterborne diseases, especially cholera. He said they had also
banned the sale of food items like unpacked bread, roast and boiled maize
on the roadside to ensure proper hygiene in the community.
[byline: Charles Akena and Josephine Anying]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Uganda showing Gulu province in the northwestern part of the
