[4] Dysentery, diarrhea - Tanzania (Zanzibar)
Date: Fri 4 Aug 2006
From: Pablo Nart <pablo.nart@terra.es>
Source: Reuters [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/IRIN/905cd0f4e714fc1bd1407d5c1925006e.htm>

An outbreak of severe dysentery and diarrhea on Tanzania's semi-autonomous
island of Zanzibar has resulted in the death of 7 children with another 454
admitted to hospital, a health official said on Fri 4 Aug 2006.
"Most of the cases were of severe dysentery and diarrhea but without
symptoms of cholera," said Dr Omar Suleiman, the director of information
policy in the Ministry of Health and Social Welfare. He said almost all the
cases registered at the Mnazi Mmoja main hospital in Stone Town originated
from the Urban District. Health officials, he said, had established that
contaminated water was to blame. Suleiman said samples of the water would
be sent to Dar es Salaam, the commercial capital of mainland Tanzania.
--
Pablo Nart
<pablo.nart@terra.es>
[A map of Tanzania showing the islands of Zanzibar adjacent to the
